## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-117">Когда <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> возвращает, следует выполнять проверки путем проверки, что границ `pointer` параметр `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-117">When <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> returns, you should perform bounds checking by verifying that the `pointer` parameter is `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-118">Если это не `null`, необходимо вызвать <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> метод в область с ограничением исполнения (CER).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-118">If it is not `null`, you must call the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method in a constrained execution region (CER).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> вызовы <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> метод и предоставляет указатель.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> calls the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and exposes the pointer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-120">В отличие от <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> метода, это не приводит к изменению текущего положения указателя.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-120">Unlike the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> method, it does not change the current position of the pointer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-121">Следующие exampledemonstrates способы использования <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> метод:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-121">The following exampledemonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> method:</span></span>  
  
```  
byte* pointer = null;  
RuntimeHelpers.PrepareConstrainedRegions();  
try {  
    MySafeBuffer.AcquirePointer(ref pointer);  
    // Use pointer here, with your own bounds checking.  
    }  
finally {  
    if (pointer != null)  
        MySafeBuffer.ReleasePointer();  
    }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-122">Если вы приводите `pointer` (который является указателем на байт) как указатель на другой тип (T \*), могут возникнуть проблемы выравнивания указатель.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-122">If you cast `pointer` (which is a pointer to a byte) as a pointer to a different type (T\*), you may have pointer alignment issues.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a9d83-123">Необходимо принять меры по проверке этот указатель всех границ.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9d83-123">You must take responsibility for all bounds checking with this pointer.</span></span>

